Package: ggbio
Version: 0.9.1
Title: Static visualization for genomic data.
Description: ggbio focuses on visualizing genomic data using basic R graphics or grid-based packages, make generic function to works on specific data structure defined in Bioconductor project. At higher levels, we implemented several graphics which could be easily used to produce some diagnostic graphics for next generation sequencing data or some other genomic data, such as grand linear view(Manhattan plot), stacked overview, mismatch pileup summary, fragment length estimation, linked view and splice summary.
Author: Tengfei Yin, Michael Lawrence, Dianne Cook
Maintainer: Tengfei Yin <yintengfei@gmail.com>
Depends: methods, biovizBase, ggplot2
Imports: methods, biovizBase, ggplot2, IRanges, GenomicRanges, GenomicFeatures, Rsamtools, BSgenome, gridExtra, scales
Suggests: BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19, TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19.knownGene
biocViews: Infrastructure, Visualization, Bioinformatics
License: GPL (>=2)
LazyLoad: Yes
